courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of the course, students will be able to

1. recognize gender as a fundamental organizing principle of society;

2. describe how gender is constructed and in what ways it influences us at individual, national and global levels;

3. explain gender in various perspectives with sound justifications;

4. theorize cultural issues from a gender perspective

5. reflect upon their life and choices.

6. Consider changes in social practices and policies that can better address gender equality

7. Evaluate the barriers and challenges in achieving gender equality in diverse cultures

Upon completion of the course, students should be able to
1. state and describe the key issues and debates in contemporary gender studies and feminist scholarship;
2. understand difficult founding texts of feminisms and gender studies;
3. apply feminist theories to contemporary gender and sexuality issues critically;
reflect upon feminist theories and formulate their own feminist perspective.

